investment board mississippi community college board previous next meet the executive team nsparcs staff includes an executive team as well as university professors, data analysts, software developers, technical writers, it professionals, and many others to provide the appropriate expertise for a wide variety of projects and innovative solutions. dr. domenico "mimmo" parisi executive director dr. parisi is a professor of sociology and executive director of nsparc. dr. parisi is also the executive director of the state longitudinal data system state data clearinghouse. he received his ph.d. from the pennsylvania state university. dr. parisi is a nationally and internationally recognized applied demographer. he represents the 21st century scholar with a focus on restructuring the role of social scientists beyond their academic pursuits to become problem solvers for public policy, economic development, and social problems that affect individuals and societies. under dr. parisis leadership, nsparc brings together expertise that focuses on the advance of methods and analytical techniques to transform "big data" into smart data raising the theoretical and empirical understanding of how individuals, groups, and society think and behave. dr. parisis work has appeared in top journals in his field, including american sociological review, demography, social forces, social problems, rural sociology, and social science quarterly. vitae leadership mparisi@nsparc.msstate.edu 662-325-9242 dr. michael taquino deputy executive director dr. taquino is a deputy executive director and an associate research professor at nsparc. his responsibilities include oversight of the entire applied science aspect of the center. dr. taquino has also published in top journals in his field including american sociological review, demography, social forces, social problems, rural sociology, and social science quarterly. he is an upcoming scholar in demography and applied social sciences. mtaquino@nsparc.msstate.edu 662-325-9242 dr. steve grice deputy executive director dr. grice is a deputy executive director and an associate research professor at nsparc. his responsibilities include supporting the center in planning, organizing, and directing center programs and activities; conducting research; ensuring that operational procedures are efficient and aligned with protocols, standards, and goals; managing personnel; and developing staff. dr. grice has also published in top journals in his field including demography, social forces, social problems, rural sociology, and social science quarterly. sgrice@nsparc.msstate.edu 662-325-9242 martin duclos deputy executive director mr. duclos is a deputy executive director at nsparc. his responsibilities include oversight of system design and development and data integration for practical applications in government enterprise. mduclos@nsparc.msstate.edu 662-325-9242 our works nsparc scientists and technique architectural products technique architectural products featured projects site furniture team about social feed contact menu featured projects site furniture team about social feed contact niketown in the winter of 2016, derse contracted technique architectural products to engineer and fabricate an interactive signage display for niketown nyc. the signage was intended to be the backdrop for social media posts as part of nike's social media campaign. the display is approximately 87" x 144" x 44" and constructed of 1/4" aluminum plate faces and returns with fully welded and ground seams. the future of pittsburgh the final minute of 2006 and the arrival of 2007 were accompanied in pittsburgh pa by a new event the raising of a giant glowing ball 75 feet into the sky from the top of penn avenue place. the ball is 6-foot 7-inches in diameter and is constructed with a framework of aluminum plate and a 3-form plastic-resin skin in the shape of the three rivers of pittsburgh. it has three sets of lights: exterior strobe lights, 1,100 led color kinetics light fixtures on the surface, and pulsating internal halogen lights. the interior is stuffed with electronics. raising the ball, as opposed to being dropped in new york city, symbolizes pittsburghs hope for the future. we are happy to have worked with paul levine and david alessi of pittsburgh-based architectural firm burt hill who designed the project. technique architectural products was responsible for fabrication, lighting installation, motion control, continued maintenance, and operation. monastery street park in the summer of 2008, southsides monastery street park received an artistic new addition. located on the southside slopes, monastery street park is a small plot of land overlooking downtown pittsburgh and bustling carson street. we are pleased to have worked directly with peter kreuthmeier of pittsburgh-based loysen kreuthmeier architects to construct and install an abstract representation of the south side slopes. constructed of cor-ten steel, the piece will develop a natural patina over time. the art piece itself is a topological map of the city, with through cuts and protruding steel planes depicting houses, rivers, and roads. backlit with linear led fixtures, the 50 feet of steel artwork glows at night greeting passersby as they ascend the slopes. 2010 segd award recipient 2009 architectural detail craftsmanship award of excellence recipient source: columns december 2009 2009 townie award for public space improvements, pennsylvania downtown center 2009 award of excellence in architectural detail, aia, pittsburgh chapter 8th street park 8th street park is part of the cultural trust district's growing effort to increase and promote bicycle and pedestrian traffic on penn avenue. the park is an oasis complete with water fountains, benches, bike racks, and a bike repair station, we are honored to have worked with the cultural trust gbbn edge studio and flyspace productions to fabricate and install the watercube, benches, and bike racks. photos by ben peoples industries martin luther king jr. elementary school martin luther king jr. elementary school is located in the northside neighborhood of pittsburgh. over the years the area, more particularly the school, had become a refuge to the homeless. the architecture of the school with its large cantilever roofs and open patios made it a perfect sanctuary for people seeking shelter. unfortunately the school began to be vandalized as well as destroyed making it unsafe for students to attend classes. we are pleased to have worked with renaissance 3 architects, p.c. and school officials to fabricate and install a fence to secure the school from unwanted intruders. made of galvanized tubular steel and perforated mesh, the fence allows light to still enter the school. the large patios, once unsafe, have now become areas for the children to play at recess. at night, each panel of the fence is illuminated with its own led light fixture. the led light fixtures continuously color shift, making for a spectacular sight. surpassed only by the empire state building, the martin luther king jr. elementary school security fence is the largest installation in the world of these led light fixtures. triangle park at three pnc plaza in may of 2009 a new passive park was announced to be constructed at the base of pncs newest green skyscraper, three pnc plaza. the park was intended to connect the cultural district and market square and serve as a place to sit, read, and relax. with the g-20 summit approaching, technique architectural products was contracted in july of 2009 to fabricate and install the entire parks site furniture. with a deadline of mid september 2009, the park was scheduled for completion in time to showcase pittsburghs newest jewel to president barack obama, the visiting nations leaders, and the world. in conjunction with local landscape architecture firm laquatra bonci and associates and structural engineering firm the kachele group technique engineered and fabricated decorative glass walls, bus shelter, shade canopy, large monolithic signs, numerous benches, and several hand railings. in the months following the g-20 summit, the park has become an amenity to those at three pnc plaza and the city. mad mex columbus mad mex offers high quality california-mexican cuisine made completely from scratch. complementing the fresh fare is a dining room and bar with a stylishly-inviting casual mexican atmosphere. technique architectural products helped to create this atmosphere in collaboration with semple brown design headquartered in denver, co and with pittsburgh artist rick bach our contributions include: engineering, fabrication and installation of eclectic, colorful sculptures, embellished entrance doors and canopy, a custom steel inside/outside bar, bar stools, seating, light fixtures, door pulls, coat hooks and railings. technique has made similar contributions to mad mex restaurants in pennsylvania, including state college, monroeville, and numerous locations in pittsburgh. bakery square in spring of 2009 bakery square, a new mixed-use development, received a neon illuminated channel letter sign that would serve as the crown for the new development. at the center of bakery square is the restored nabisco plant, on top of which is where the new neon sign is installed. located at the crossroads of several desirable and well-educated neighborhoods of the east end, bakery square offers tenants an exciting lifestyle environment. in conjunction with local design firm kolano design technique architectural products was contracted to install and fabricate custom channel letters and new structural steel that would be mounted to an existing refurbished billboard structure. westmoreland museum of american art from the summer of 2013 until the fall of 2015, the westmoreland museum of american art underwent a complete renovation and expansion campaign to transform the outdated museum into a fresh and updated space for artists and the community. we were honored to have worked with ennead architects laquatra bonci and associates spaulding banks project management, and keystone structural solutions to engineer, fabricate, and install the project's interior and exterior architectural metalwork. our contributions include: aluminum brise soliel, starphire glass and heavy gauge steel stair #3, steel and precast terrazzo stair #4, aluminum west window screen, aluminum cantilever sag rod and fins, aluminum and precast terrazzo reception desk, aluminum site fencing, and stainless steel handrails. southside slopes gateway located at 18th and josephine streets, the south side slopes gateway pylon marks the entrance to one of pittsburghs unique neighborhoods. designed by peter kreuthmeier of pittsburgh-based loysen kreuthmeier architects the pylon is constructed of an anodized aluminum inner prism with a cor-ten steel outer shell. above the prism, an aluminum tensegrity structure holds a solar panel responsible for powering the pylons lights and electronics. inside the prism, batteries store the energy to illuminate the pylon at night commissioned by the south side slopes neighborhood association (ssna) the pylon was realized by a diverse and specialized design team. techniques responsibilities included the engineering and fabrication of the anodized aluminum inner prism, cor-ten outer shell, and project installation. the andy warhol museum reception desk during the holiday season of 2008 the andy warhol museum of pittsburgh contracted technique to fabricate an intricate and unique new reception desk for their main lobby. the new desk, designed by gbbn edge studio was to serve as an aesthetic piece of artwork as well as a functional piece of furniture. the entire desk was designed and engineered using rhino3d and fabricated from rolled aluminum plate in 18 separate pieces. the countertop is constructed of thermoformed 1 thick acrylic with continuous color kinetics edge lighting. the thermoformed acrylic tops softly flow into each other as the desk changes elevation. the gentle transitions of the translucent acrylic against the stark contrast of the sharp and opaque aluminum desk provide an interesting interaction between materials. in september of 2009 as pittsburgh welcomed the g-20 summit and the world, the warhol lobby was used as a party venue for the first wives of all the nations visiting leaders. 2009 architectural detail craftmanship award of excellence recipient source: columns december 2009 seton hill university helix designed by kma design technique was honored to fabricate and install a new donor sculpture for seton hill university that recognized donations associated with the new health sciences center. the monument is approximately 120" tall x 48" diameter and constructed of rolled and formed .5" thick aluminum w/ etched stainless steel plaques wrapping the exterior faces and base. pitt honors college during the 2002-03 academic year, the university of pittsburghs university honors college offices on the 35th and 36th floors of the cathedral of learning underwent a major renovation. working with a design by the pittsburgh firm, rothschild doyno collaborative technique architectural products built the staircase and railing system between the two floors. upon the projects completion, techniques craftsmanship was recognized by the city of pittsburgh and the historic review commission with a historic preservation award. technique architectural products used laser-cut layers of steel with a rich patina to give the project an old world look, creating a tie to the craftsmanship of samuel yellin whose wrought iron work decorates the commons room at the base of the building. ken doyno, lead architect for the renovations, called the craft and technology of the old and new ironwork in the cathedral the pinnacle of the craft of wrought ironwork. techniques owner and founder, ray appleby, was moved by the project. it was really a special opportunity to be involved in such a momentous project; one that will be around for years to come, he said. the cathedral of learning, a historic landmark, is the second-tallest education building in the world 42 stories and 535 feet tall. it is also the geographic and traditional heart of the campus. pitt legacy exhibit in the fall of 2006 a new permanent exhibit was installed on the first floor of the university of pittsburghs alumni hall. the exhibit consists of two interactive computer kiosks, pitt in the world and the pitt experience, each 10 feet tall and eight feet in diameter with multiple rear-projection computer touch screens. viewers can learn about the many accomplishments of pitt alumni, faculty and students during its almost 200-year history. the information is organized by field of endeavor plus an animated timeline which locates each individual and program in pitts history. the exhibit instills a sense of pride and possibilities in the pitt community and pittsburgh. we are happy to have worked with pittsburgh designer tom malacki of thoughtform design and with university officials to fabricate the kiosks from wood, steel, and brass, and to incorporate the computer hardware donated by dell corporation. pitts legacy gallery is the only one of its kind in the united states carnegie mellon university cafe the caf is located on the carnegie mellon university campus in pittsburgh, pa. we are pleased to have worked with greg george of the pittsburgh architectural firm pfaffmann associates on the curved aluminum signage that compliments the existing rotunda. the sign and vertical curvilinear elements are all made from aluminum. the main sign incorporates push-through frosted acrylic lettering illuminated from the rear with white leds, whereas the caf text is typical channel-letter construction also illuminated with leds. the curvilinear elements are accented by red led strips, instead of the more customary neon lighting. led strip lighting is becoming quite popular for indoor border lighting and outdoor accents biology summer programs since 1993, broadreach has offered educational adventure summer programs for high school students and middle school students as well as summer study abroad programs for college students they have taken thousands of students on a wide variety of adventures in over 35 countries including the islands of the caribbean, central and south america, australia, fiji, the solomon islands, india, china, egypt, south africa, france, canada and the bahamas. broadreachs adventure travel summer camps for teens offer more exploration, learning and discovery than traditional teen tours or traditional teen summer camps. their teen trips include caribbean summer camps scuba diving summer camps sailing summer camps costa rica summer camps and teen community service camps worldwide. broadreachs academic summer camps all qualify for college credit and include marine biology summer camps as well as a variety of foreign language summer camps including spanish summer camps and french summer camps broadreachs summer programs and college study abroad programs combine the finest elements of experiential learning, traditional classroom learning, and service learning with international travel and cultural exchange to create extraordinary expeditions. this is how we take our students to a new latitude every summer. live chat software login call us request info search that not only leaves you feeling relaxed and revived, but helps you make memories to last a lifetime. the bucket list: vail and beaver creek 15 activities you must try on your trip to vail or beaver creek when you're surrounded by the majesty of the rockies, anything is possible. so much that it can be tough to decide where to start. what should go on your vail valley bucket list? we have a few ideas. we asked world champion skier lindsey vonn and other high-profile vail beaver creek locals share their favorite activities on the mountains and in the valley. here are 15 to add to your "must-do" list. ski or snowboard, of course. but after that, reserve some time to relax in the village, says ski champ lindsey vonn. "it's fun to mill around vail village and hang out on a sunny patio after a hard workout," she says. take a horse-drawn sleigh ride. for an unforgettable rocky mountain experience, join bearcat stables for a horse-drawn sleigh ride and gourmet dinner at their restored historic ranch, conveniently located 15 minutes west of beaver creek, colorado in the beautiful cordillera valley. mush! mush! vail valley local heather brown, 42, says that when guests visit, she likes to take them dog sledding. it's a great way to explore a lot of terrain without crowds, and the dogs are incredible, she says. mountain musher runs on a private trail in wolcott, 10 miles west of beaver creek. the sleds will take you through glades of aspen and pine trees. without other traffic like snowmobiles, guests often see wildlife including fox, coyote, deer and elk. colorado ski snowboard museum. check out artifacts of the ski industry, see who made it to the hall of fame, and learn some local history here. it's amazing to see how far skiing and snowboarding has evolved over the years. go fishing any time of year. "i'm also getting into fly fishing in the valley," says lindsey vonn. "my dog leo joins me for that too, although he tends to scare away the fish." there are a number of fishing outfitters throughout vail, avon, and beaver creek with guides who will get you casting in no time. visit mccoy park in beaver creek. mccoy park, which is accessed via the strawberry park lift, is considered one of beaver creek's best-kept secrets. the park features more than 32 kilometers of groomed and rustic trails for cross-country skiing and snowshoeing. and, since it's nestled between beaver creek and bachelor gulch villages, mccoy park offers amazing views of three mountain ranges at once. minturn cellars winery. several wine aficionados we talked to suggested this hidden gem, housed in a historic 1900 building in minturn. call for tasting room times and the cellar's current wine list: (970) 827-4065 book an adventure session. some guests hire an instructor to ski with them all day just to cut lift lines and find the best powder, and it's not a bad idea. but vail offers something even better. "adventure sessions" are a hybrid private/group experience for experienced skiers focused on touring and making the most of the day rather than on instruction. you can still cut lines, find the best conditions and terrain, navigate the huge mountain easily, and even gain some pointers, but at a lower price point ($150 per person with no more than 5 skiers). get custom fit for cowboy boots or hat in vail or beaver creek. western wear shops are a staple in the vail valley, and when you walk in, the experts will custom fit you for the boots or cowboy hat of your dreams (steamed and molded to conform to your head so you know it looks perfect). take a free, guided snowshoe tour from the nature discovery center located at the top of the eagle bahn gondola. tours are offered daily beginning mid-december and are led by an expert naturalist from walking mountains, a non-profit science learning center that promotes environmental stewardship through natural science education. attend the vail mountain games (as a spectator or participant). held in summer and winter, these events bring professional and amateur athletes to the vail valley for several days of adventure, competition, demos, music, art, and immersion in the mountain lifestyle. it's truly a bucket-list experience. join the friday afternoon club. celebrity chef kelly liken says she and her family like to attend the fac at the top of the vail gondola every summer. "there is live music, and the view is breathtaking. there are many different kinds of hikes in the area as well. the north trail is a personal favorite. it is demanding at times but when the flowers are in bloom you don't notice that you are out of breath as much!" she says. ski the minturn mile. the minturn mile is one of the most famous off-piste ski runs in the world. it is accessed from the top of chairs 3 or 7 on vail mountain and then by taking the out-of-bounds access gate at the top of the turn on lost boy trail. from there, you'll descend more than 3,100 feet in elevation to an unofficial trailhead near the minturn saloon. note: only try this if you're an expert skier with backcountry knowledge. this route is beyond the bounds of vail resort and not serviced by ski patrol. go biking year-round. you didn't think mountain biking was a winter activity? think again. locals like seth johnson, 31, an avid cyclist, recommend snow biking in winter with fat, studded tires, or using the ski bikes provided at the adventure center at vail. in summer, there's plenty of sweet singletrack lacing the slopes too, and sports shops throughout town rent equipment if you don't have your own, he says. come back in the summer. don't assume the fun ends when the snow melts. the vail valley, including beaver creek, has a full menu of activities in the summer. concerts, hikes, festivals, or just beautiful places to hang out and enjoy the scenery abound. "i love walking my dog leo by the river in summertime," says lindsey vonn. ski like a local the inside scoop to plan your ski vacation ski like a local we asked a handful of ski instructors and patrollers to give us the inside scoop: what's the best way to ski vail or beaver creek find the powder stashes, and avoid lines? here's what they had to say: get out there early (before 9:00 a.m.) and you'll avoid the most lines. you'll be on the mountain before ski school starts, and before the commuters from denver arrive. if you can't go before 9:00 a.m., wait until 11:00. if you miss the early window, it's better to hang out, eat a big breakfast and grab a lift up later in the morning when the crowds dissipate and many skiers and riders are starting to take a break. on busy days or holidays, consider skipping the gondola and ride chairs instead. often it's quicker to take side chairs up the mountain and traverse a little bit rather than wait in a long gondola line. don't hop into the closest lift line. as you're descending toward the lift, scan the maze and see which line looks smallest and aim for that one. oftentimes, skiers and riders go for the closest, easiest line, but it's not always the quickest, experts say. know the best runs. on vail, the ski instructors we talked to said it's great to start on riva ridge, a long, twisting groomed black that will get you warmed up and excited for the day ahead. another good choice, especially if you're based in lionshead, is simba trail. if the back bowls are your goal, consider going straight to blue sky basin and working your way back toward the west, opposite of the tourists' usual traffic flow. be bold. finally, all the experts we talked with agree: don't be afraid to walk up to staff members at vail or jawaharlal nehru technological university hyderabad jawaharlal nehru technological university hyderabad welcome to jawaharlal nehru technological university hyderabad jawaharlal nehru technological university, hyderabad, was established on 2 nd october 1972 by the legislature of the state of andhra pradesh as the first technological university in the country. it has been in the forefront for the past 44 years in providing quality technological education of relevance in the state of andhra pradesh. after 36 years of existence it was restructured into 4 different universities by the government vide government ordinance no.13, dated 18 th august 2008 and act of state legislature no.30 dated september 2008 and this new university has been designated as jawaharlal nehru technological university hyderabad (jntuh) jntuh is situated in a sprawling 89-acre campus at kukatpally, hyderabad. it has now 4 constituent engineering colleges, one at hyderabad, one at kondagattu (jagithyal), one at manthani and one at sultanpur (medak dist.) and 15 other constituent units on hyderabad campus. jntuh offers b.tech. programmes in 24 disciplines and b.pharm at ug level; integrated 5-year dual degree masters programme; m.tech. programmes in 68 disciplines, m.pharm. in 11 disciplines; m.sc. in 10 disciplines; mca, mba and double degree programmes at p.g. level; in addition to the offer of m.s., m.phil., ph.d. research programmes in various disciplines of engineering, technology, science, management and humanities. jntuh has 423 affiliated colleges spread over the telangana state. jntuh has more than 3.50 lakhs students on rolls. the university has memoranda of university with many national and international organizations. administration prof. a. venugopal reddy vice-chancellor dr. der marke travelworks zhlt die travelplus group gmbh zu den fhrenden anbietern von auslandsprogrammen, die reisen und lernen bzw. reisen, arbeiten und lernen kombinieren. wir kooperieren mit einem netzwerk anerkannter partnerschulen und organisationen in zahlreichen lndern weltweit. jhrlich reisen tausende von auslandsbegeisterten und interkulturell interessierten menschen mit uns, um im gastland ihrer wahl in kultur und sprache einzutauchen, mehr ber den alltag und die menschen vor ort zu erfahren, mit ihnen zu lernen, zu leben und zu arbeiten, den eigenen horizont zu erweitern und dabei eine unvergessliche, erlebnis- wie lehrreiche zeit jenseits der eigenen landesgrenzen zu verbringen. travelplus group gmbh with its brand travelworks ranges amongst the leading tour operators combining travelling, learning and working abroad. in cooperation with a network of renowned partners we run programmes in many countries all around the globe. every year thousands of travel and language enthusiasts travel with us to explore foreign cultures, countries and languages, to live and work with the locals abroad, to gain intercultural knowledge and to have an exciting time in one of so many intriguing countries around the world. travelworks travelworker entdecken die welt per working-holiday, d.h. sie reisen und arbeiten im gastland. whrend die arbeit in den entwickelteren lndern europas, nordamerikas, australien und neuseeland bezahlt wird, engagieren sich travelworker in lndern lateinamerikas, afrikas und asiens ehrenamtlich in projekten, die der entwicklung, bildung oder auch dem tierschutz vor ort zugute kommen. mit einer breiten palette von sprachreisen, auslandspraktika und summer camps fr schler bietet travelworks zielgruppengerecht programme fr erwachsene, kinder, jugendliche und firmenkunden an. zur auswahl stehen verschiedene destinationen weltweit, so dass wir kurse fr sieben weltsprachen englisch, franzsisch, spanisch, italienisch, portugiesisch, russisch und chinesisch anbieten knnen. rund um den globus bietet travelworks schlern die mglichkeit im rahmen eines high school-aufenthalts erste mehrmonatige auslandserfahrung an einer gastschule und bei einer gastfamilie zu sammeln. mit dem summer school programm haben schler die mglichkeit in ihren sommerferien das leben an einer high school im ausland fr einige wochen kennenzulernen. mit dem programm internship usa organisieren wir berufsttigen und studierenden einen fachpraktikumsaufenthalt in den usa. travelworkers discover the world per working-holiday. while some travelworkers chose to spend a working-holiday in europe, north america, australia or new zealand and get paid for their work, others employ their time in latin america, africa and asia on a voluntary basis. they help in projects fostering e.g. local development, education or wildlife protection. offering language travel, internships and summer camps abroad carpe diem runs a wide selection of programmes for adults, juniors and executives. we operate language trips to different destinations worldwide covering seven languages: english, french, spanish, italian, russian, portuguese and chinese. travelworks high school programmes throughout the world give teenagers a first opportunity to experience school and life abroad. during the summer school, young students can experience life at a high school overseas for a few weeks in their summer holidays. students and employees wishing to gain work experience in the us are catered by our programme internship usa. travelplus group home home ber uns increasing prices, businesses and consumers are looking for more ways to save money. as a result, the sale of compatible printer consumables is increasing but many people are still unaware of the serious implications of using non-branded inks, toners and drums in their machines. will using cheaper compatible products invalidate my printer warranty? it depends. using compatible consumables inyour printer may not invalidate the warranty. however any damage caused to your printer by the use of third party consumables will not be repaired under the terms of the printers warranty. it is wise to check the manufactures website for warranty terms. how are compatible toner cartridges made? some compatible cartridges are simply refilled the casing is cracked open and refilled with new toner. compatibles produced in this way are generally poor quality, unreliable and often lower capacity compared with branded cartridges. refurbished cartridges are completely stripped down and rebuilt from scratch, using reconditioned components, or brand new ones where necessary. the cartridges are reassembled to the original manufacturers specifications and given a full load of toner; asa result, cartridges produced in this way can be at least equal in build quality to the originals. three main risks with compatible toners: leaking. these cartridges are normally a refilled genuine cartridges. seals may not be as good as when the toner was originally filled. damage to the fuser. if the cartridge has been refilled with toner that has different characteristics, the toner can stick the q collective pr agency and reputation management please enable js home about us team what we do recent work blog let's talk seeing the big picture "i work with about a dozen pr companies in my assorted roles and without doubt the q collective always produces the goods, on time and well presented. which is something you cant say about every pr firm! the team is always fun and good to deal with and responds to requests promptly and efficiently, which, when you are working to deadlines, is pretty important." mike pryce, business/property editor and chief features writer, worcester news powerful performance "mark and his team completely engrossed themselves in the battle of evesham festival. without the q collective's involvement, it would have not been the success it was. they provided resource and advice, gave round the clock assistance and produced on-point comms which hit the right audiences in both content and to all target media." antonia coles, festival co-ordinator, battle of evesham 2015 "wychavon district council appointed mark and his team to provide pr support to evesham town centre throughout the replacement works of abbey road bridge. in short, the agency was highly effective in encouraging local residents to be proud of evesham even becoming advocates for their town and at the same time, sending clear messages that eveshams shops, bars, restaurants, hotels and other leisure attractions were very much open for business. "the agency promoted eveshams unique festival offering and used these to differentiate the town from nearby and other regional destinations. the team maintained regular and effective communication and sustained good relations with local, regional and national media throughout. they informed and educated audiences as to the range and variety of retail and leisure outlets, services and facilities available in the town. most importantly, the team monitored and helped to mitigate any negative publicity/comments that arose throughout the period of the contract. "they did all this via traditional and digital media. the bridge works overran considerably creating a huge amount of critical comments, especially on social media. the agency was able to respond to this by creating continuing positive media coverage of events, business successes and promotional offers. many businesses benefited from free pr as a result and the resource was very much missed once the works were finally completed." shawn riley, evesham business partnerships manager, wychavon district council basepoint crab apple way vale business park evesham wr11 1gp 01386 443300 navigate home what we do recent work blog privacy policy sitemap about us company team contact the q collective 2017

street melbourne vic 3000 sydney level 6, 139 macquarie st sydney nsw 2000 home connect services about contact careers agility applications provide applications, technology products, and services to the capital markets industry. we enhance, streamline and automate organisations existing work practices to improve the appeal of their core products and boost performance. connect connect is agilitys proprietary application platform. it allows organisations to make business processes more efficient and enrich data capacity. all connect applications are fully integrated with reports and external integration partners. connect applications include: portfolio summary and update brokerage schedules and demographics portfolio reporting margin lending interfaces customer onboarding customer relationship management capital raising and commission management app category account and portfolio management advisor management and utilities order and securities management and reporting tools middle office, operational functions and integrations account and portfolio management advisor management and utilities order and securities management and reporting tools middle office, operational functions and integrations services our software development approach is based around agile practices. this approach emphasizes prototyping and rapid, iterative build cycles rather than extensive documentation, long development cycles, and single end project deliverables. consulting agility has extensive experience in capital markets technologies; in particular, cash equities and exchange traded options processing both in australia and offshore. agility can provide consulting services across a wide range of functions such as asx required audits of bcp and recovery solutions, corporate actions processing as well as consulting on bookings, settlement and fx processing. we will advise you in developing your technology solution, and support you throughout the entire transaction life-cycle. agile reporting services information stored in financial systems can have a profound impact on an organisations ability to enhance existing business practices. agility builds a suite of customised reports tailored to your exact requirements using the live data that resides in your back-end systems. this wealth of information allows a business to become more proactive towards customers, tailor marketing strategies and respond to changes in the regulatory environment. agile support services agility provides support for 3rd party products and in-house developed applications. our tiered product support models allow us to tailor solutions based on the style of application and the level of commitment you need. additionally, by providing the expertise necessary to manage and maintain in-house developed applications, agility can ensure their relevance is maintained from both a business and technological perspective. about us agility applications provides consulting, business analysis, software development and cyber resilience services that enables organisations to enhance, streamline and automate their existing work practices with the aim of improving the overall appeal of their core products and enhancing their performance. our purpose is to assist our clients to maximise the return on their it investment while enhancing their overall value proposition in the market-place through the development of intelligent software solutions that streamline business processes and reduce cost. agility applications is an it services company created to provide organisations with a viable, realistic alternative for the development of applications. agility applications pty ltd is a wholly owned subsidiary of the industry leading investment and superannuation platform provider hub24 limited (asx: hub). agile products and services agility provides a range of in-house and third-party products and services for the financial services industry. from compliance and data warehouse applications through to customised reporting and product support services. agile development services our software development methodology is based around agile practices. this methodology places a heavy emphasis on prototyping and rapid, iterative build cycles rather than extensive documentation with long development cycles and single end of project deliverables. some of the benefits realised by adopting this style of development include: customer satisfaction via swift, continuous delivery of useful software working software is delivered frequently (weeks rather than months) working software is the principal measure of progress cooperation between the business defining the requirements and the people developing the solution continuous attention to technical excellence and good design regular and efficient adaptation to changing circumstances. technology designed for specific business needs, time or budget constraints or existing infrastructure. agility clients agility now delivers technology products and services to more than 175 groups australia-wide and has a direct license relationship with approximately 70 groups. the rest access agility connect framework via wholesale master licenses made available to a number of clearing groups. connect now has 1500 unique users across the 140 groups enabled. agility timeline 2007 2008 2009 2010 2011 2012 to develop stand-alone billing app and trade capture and reporting app for sydney and melbourne clients. australian reporting systems acquisition july 2007 june 2008 ars contract executed with subsequent migration of clients and products over to agility. first sydney staff hired april 2009 november 2009 secured it design contract and subsequently whole of business it support contract for young people surveys view now catholic night at petco august 18, 2017 learn more 1 2 1 1 2 3 latest news 1 2 3 4 our mission jesus is the good news of salvation for people of every race and nation, every language and culture. he passes on to his disciples in every age the mission which he received from the father. to each of us he says: as the father has sent me, so i send you (jn 20:21). jesus saw himself anointed for mission by the spirit, and the missionary mandate is a sending forth in the spirit. he is addressing us when he says: you will receive power when the holy spirit comes upon you, and you will be my witnesses in jerusalem, throughout judea and samaria, and to the ends of the earth. (acts 1:8). go, therefore, and make disciples of all nations teaching them to observe all that i have commanded you. and behold, i am with you always. (mt 28:19-20). go out to all the world and tell the good news. (mk 16:15) the mission of the church is a participation in the mission of jesus, the one and only savior of the world. he stated clearly: i am the way and the truth and the life. no one comes to the father except through me. smarihasta 10 august 2017 tim basket putri sma negeri 8 malang mencatat hasil mengesankan pada penampilan perdana mereka di honda dbl east java series 2017south region malang. menghadapi sman 1 kedungwaru tulungagung, smarihasta (nama lain sman 8 malang) menang telak 33-7.kemenangan itu dicapai berkat penampilan penuh percaya diri yang diperagakan pemain tim basket putri sman 8 malang sejak awal pertandingan. bahkan, mereka mampu menutup kuarter pertama dengan keunggulan 9-0.dominasi sman 8 malang masih berlanjut di tiga kuarter berikutnya. hingga akhirnya mereka mampu mengunci kemenangan dengan skor telak 33-7.pelatih tim basket putri sman 8 malang catur agung menyatakan, hasil laga ini sesuai dengan ekspektasinya. anakanak bermain sangat disiplin dan komunikasi pemain juga bagus sehingga bisa menang, kata dia usai pertandingan.meski begitu, catur mengungkapkan, para pemainnya belum menunjukkan seluruh potensi pada laga melawan sman 1 kedungwaru. anak-anak masih terlihat nervous, terutama empat pemain kelas x. sebab, ini pengalaman kali pertama mereka, ujarnya.dia pun berharap, performa sman 8 malang bisa lebih baik saat menghadapi sman 1 blitar, lawan mereka berikutnya. itu tim yang bagus. makanya kami harus mempersiapkan dengan matang. ada beberapa yang harus kami benahi dan pastinya meningkatkan performa bermain, kata dia.sementara itu, kapten tim basket putri sman 8 malang pramata alvina me nyatakan, yang kurang dari laga me lawan sman 1 kedungwaru adalah soal koordinasi saja. koordinasi dan kom un ikasi masih perlu ditingkatkan lagi, pungkasnya. (adk/c2/muf)... bhawikarsu kalah terhormat 10 august 2017 laga bergengsi terjadi di honda developmental basketball league (dbl) east java series 2017south region kemarin (9/8). dua tim dengan tradisi basket yang bagus, yakni sman 3 malang dan sman 1 boyolangu, tulungagung, harus adu kuat dalam perebutan juara grup b.dalam laga yang dihadiri sekitar 2.000 suporter itu, sman 1 boyolangu berhasil memenangi laga dengan skor tipis 24-15. meski kalah, sman 3 kota malang tetap lolos ke babak playoff 16 besar. tim ini posisinya berada satu setrip di bawah sman 1 boyolangu, tulungagung, yang menjadi juara grup b.bhawikarsujulukan sman 3 malang seolah-olah kalah terhormat. ini karena sejak kuarter pertama, tim ini membuat sengit dengan permainan yang ngotot. di kuarter ini, iman bramantya dan kawankawan kalah dengan selisih skor 6-10. di kuarter kedua, perolehan sekolah ini jeblok dengan hanya bisa menambah satu poin.kuarter ketiga berakhir dengan skor 9-17 untuk sma boyolangu. pada kuarter terakhir, dengan ketenangan serta kematangan bermain, sman 1 boyolangu sukses mengakhiri skor dengan poin 24-15. pertandingannya me mang sangat menarik karena membuktikan siapa yang pantas menj adi juara dan runner-up, kata pelatih tim basket putra sman 3 malang wahyudiono setelah laga kemarin.menurut dia, masing-masing tim mempunyai skill yang sama bagus. oleh karena itu, tim pelatih harus adu cerdik dalam menjalankan strategi. yang membuat kami kalah adalah pemain terlalu tergesa-gesa, imbuhnya. menurut dia, jika anak asuhnya bisa bermain dengan tenang, hasilnya akan berbeda. jika pemain bisa tenang, shoot dan passing-nya akan lebih baik lagi, pungkasnya.sementara itu, pelatih sman 1 boyolangu jonathan ristian menyatakan, meski menang hasil kemarin belum sesuai ekspektasinya. ini masih jauh, meski kami juara grup, katanya. menurut dia, masih ada banyak kelemahan. ini tentu yang harus diperbaiki sebelum nanti di pertandingan 16 besar. soal transisi dari tim masih lemah, kapan pemain harus menyerang dan bertahan, itulah yang akan kami benahi, tandasnya. (adk/c2/riq)... 3 laga do or die untuk 3 tiket playoff 10 august 2017 kemarin (9/8) di babak utama honda dbl east java series 2017north region tiga tiket menjadi milik tim yang berhasil menundukkan lawannya lewat laga do or die.bara selamatkan smantass lewat free throwlaga do or die pertama mempertemukan smamda sidoarjo, sebutan sma muhammadiyah 2 sidoarjo, dengan smantass, julukan sma negeri 17 surabaya.smamda sidoarjo lebih membuka perolehan lewat layup dari center muhammad william bintang. pada menit kelima, danny maulana, guard smantass, mulai mengambil alih permainan. bahkan, danny sempat berhasil mencetak dua bola lewat shooting mautnya. kuarter pertama ditutup dengan poin dari yoga fikri firas yang berhasil memanfaatkan bola rebound. smamda sidoarjo unggul sementara 10-5 atas smantass.pada kuarter kedua, kedua tim mulai bermain cukup terbuka. mereka saling bertukar serangan dan getol menjaga jantung pertahanan. hingga turun minum pada kuarter ketiga, kedua tim bertahan imbang 20-20.memasuki kuarter keempat, laga berlangsung makin sengit. smamda sidoarjo bermain cukup emosional sehingga memberi celah lawan untuk mendapatkan free throw.pada 30 detik terakhir pertandingan, muhammad bara, forward smantass, datang bak juru selamat bagi timnya. dua kali kesempatan free throw dieksekusi bara dengan baik. hingga akhirnya, laga ditutup dengan skor 26-24 untuk kemenangan smantass. defense lawan kurang gercep. itulah yang menjadi celah.  ujar danny maulana, kapten smantass. evaluasi diri kunci kemenangan sixteenrunner-up grup g putri akhirnya direbut skuad sma negeri 16 surabaya. kemarin sixteen, sebutan sma negeri 16 surabaya, berhasil menundukkan lawannya, smantass, dengan skor akhir 26-2.walau lolos, kami tetap tidak bisa tidur nyenyak. banyak sekali pr yang harus dikerjakan. melihat permainan tadi, saya kecewa karena game play tidak berjalan, rebound-nya jelek, sampai finishingnya pun tidak memuaskan, jelas saddam nanda, assistant coach sixteen.yap, keberhasilan sixteen itu tidak mudah didapatkan begitu saja. apalagi, sixteen sempat mengalami kekalahan ketika melawan skuad sma negeri 19 surabaya, yang juga lolos ke babak playoff sebagai jawara grup g putri.di game terakhir ini, setiap pemain melakukan banyak sekali kesalahan kecil. misalnya, kami seharusnya bisa menghasilkan poin, tap malah tidak dapat memanfaatkannya. teamwork lebih baik daripada pertandingan sebelumnya sih. kami lebih banyak berbagi bola dan sudah mulai mengurangi ego masing-masing, ucap zahra sania, kapten sixteen.sejak awal kuarter pertama, sixteen memang berhasil unggul atas smantass. bahkan, kuarter pertama ditutup dengan skor 8-0 untuk keunggulan sementara sixteen. bahkan, hingga akhir kuarter ketiga, smantass sama sekali belum menambah perolehan. baru saat memasuki kuarter keempat, smantass mendapatkan kesempatan free throw yang akhirnya mampu dieksekusi.(rno/nao/c14/dhs)... sebagai debutan smanis putri tebar ancaman 10 august 2017 tim basket 3x3 sman 1 sumberlawang harus puas gagal meloloskan seluruh wakilnya di babak 8 besar loop 3x3 competiton yang akan dipusatkan di sritex arena (11-19/8) mendatang.dalam sesi roadshow loop 3x3 compe. titon di mikael sport center kemarin (9/8), ternyata dua wakil tim berjuluk smanis tersebut gagal meraih hasil yang sama.tim putra smanis kekalahan 3-6 dari tim sman 1 boyolali. hasil ini tentu menjadi pembelajaran berarti bagi tim ini. beruntung smanis putri memberi asa agar wakil sekolah ini masih bisa unjuk gigi di sritex arena nantinya.tim basket putri sekolah bermarkas di jalan solo-purwodadi km.27, sumberlawang, sragen tersebut sukses menang atas sman 1 karanganyar (smansakra). dalam babak normal kedua tim imbang 0-0, dibabak overtime, smanis putri akhirnya sukses meraih dua poin pertama dan menutup laga dengan keungglan 2-0 dari smansakra. hasil ini membawa mereka merebut tiket ke babak 8 besar.tim yang beranggotakan vivi wulandari, melisa, indah pramiswari, dan ifah mukaromah ini akan menantang tim sman 3 solo yang sudah lebih dulu aman di babak 8 besar.untuk persiapan di loop ini latihannya hanya dua kali saja, tapi kalau untuk ikut kejuaraan serupa (3x3) sudah sering. dari komposisi ini kami sudah ikut enam kali turnamen berbeda. prestasi terbaik adalah fantastic four saat main di hartono mall, beber kapten tim sman 1 sumberlawang, vivi kepada radar solo usai pertandingan kemarin.jika nantinya menang di babak 8 besar, smanis putri sudah harus bersiap diri. hal ini mengingat salah satu dari hasil pertandingan sman 4 solo melawan sman 5 solo kana jadi lawan mereka nantinya di babak semifinal.perebutan tiket menuju semifinal juga akan diperebutkan oleh tim putri sman 1 sukoharjo b melawan sman 3 klaten, maupun tim regpac (julukan sama regina pacis) m endapat hadangan lawan berat melawan mantan juara turnamen ini dua musim lalu, yakni sma muhammadiyah 1 solo.kalau di turnamen ini target kami hanya main sebaik mungkin. sebenarnya ingin ikut di turnamen dbl-nya tapi karena tidak punya tim dance jadi fokus kami meraih juara tinggal di 3x3-nya. semoga bisa membawa nama sekolah harus di sritex nanti, harap vivi. (nik)... persaingan tiga lawan tiga, juga berjalan ketat 10 august 2017 tahun lalu tim basket putra sman 1 boyolali (smansaboy) sukses menjadi juara loop 3x3 competition. tahun ini tim ini kembali hadir dan memasang target yang sama. mental juara benar-benar mereka perlihatkan. di laga perdana yang digelar di mikael sport center kemarin (9/8), tim asal kota susu ini sukses mengalahkan tim sman 1 sumberlawang (6-3).bahkan tiket menuju babak delapan besar berhasil mereka genggam, setelah mengalahkan wakil tuan rumah, yakni smk st mikael b.sempat tertinggal 4-1, tim ini berhasil bangkit hingga menyamakan kedudukan menjadi 4-4. di babak overtime smansa boy sukses meraih dua poin lebih dulu, dan mengakhiri laga dengan kemenangan 6-4.sayang jawara musim lalu, yakni tim basket putri sman 1 slogohimo (smansago) wonogiri absen di musim ini. walau begitu wakil putra sekolah ini ternyata membuktikan diri akan kualitas skill individu, sekolah yang bermarkas di jl raya slogohimo-purwantoro, slogohimo, wonogiri tersebut. smansago putra sukses menang di pertandingan kemarin, atas smk st mikael tim c (5-3), dan smk pl leonardo (3-0). atas hasil ini, smansago akan ditantang tim smkn 2 solo di babak 8 besar. dimana calon lawannya tersebut, kemarin menang di babak 16 besar atas sman 4 solo (2-0).semoga para peserta (loop 3x3) yang bertanding, bisa bermain dengan sangat sportif dan penuh semangat, ucap perwakilan dari smk st mikael, aris.sayang kompetisi tiga lawan tiga ini, mico (julukan smk st mikael) harus legowo karena gagal mengirimkan wakilnya di babak 8 besar loop 3x3 competition musim ini.menurunkan tiga timnya, ternyata satu persatu tim ini gagal menjegal para tamunya. tim a mico kalah dari sman 2 sragen (smanda) dengan skor 5-1, sementara tim c mico kalah dari sman 1 slogohimo, hingga tim b mico harus mengakui keunggulan sman 1 boyolali.sementara itu berbeda dengan tahun sebelumnya, dimana para juara akan mengitu kejuaraan nasional dengan para pemenang loop 3x3 competition dari geional lainnya di surabaya. tahun ini ternyata hanya akan dipilih dua most valueable player (mvp) yang diberangkatkan ke surabaya, untuk mengikuti loop 3x3 national camp.kalau sebelumnya, seluruh anggota tim yang diberangkatkan. tahun ini hanya mvp saja. satu mvp putra dan satu mvp putri. keduanya wajib mengikuti loop 3x3 national camp di surabaya, ujar basketball operation honda dbl central java series, syarifudin. (nik)... debutan langsung tebar ancaman 10 august 2017 tim cewek sma van lith magelang membuka peluang mereka untuk lolos ke babak selanjutnya di ajang loop 3x3 competition yang merupakan supporting event honda dbl central java series north region 2017 kali ini.skuad sma van lith magelang sebagai pendatang baru diisi oleh anastasia a s (5), regina vika m (4), vanesha f f t (6), dan jansqualime r p (7). satu poin dibuka oleh van lith melalui anastasia. namun sedes sapientiae membalikkan keadaan dengan memimpin 3-1. sayang permainan sedes sapientiae tidak berkembang. justru van lith berhasil membalikkan keadaan dengan poin yang beruntun.skor 7-3 untuk kemenangan van lith. coach sma van lith magelang edwin budi rahmanto tampak puas dengan hasil tersebut karena yang mereka lawan termasuk tim yang tidak bisa dianggap enteng. strateginya yang penting kita main, lakukan saja sebaik mungkin. pokoknya siap main tampil sebaikbaiknya, terangnya.ia menambahkan untuk laga selanjutnya masih menerapkan strategi yang sama dengan fokus ke pertahanan. sebagai pendatang baru, ia mengharapkan timnya tidak terkena demam panggung, apalagi lawan selanjutnya pasti lebih kuat.pada laga cowok, loop 3x3 mempertemukan sma tri tunggal semarang (a) versus sma terang bangsa semarang (b). laga ini berjalan sengit dengan skor yang saling menyusul. kedua tim saling menampilkan aksiaksi individu yang menawan. kapten tim tri tunggal nic olas menggempur lawan dengan memberi tembakan satu poin.namun susul menyusul angka tidak bisa dielakkan karena penampilan impresif kedua tim. skor 5-5 bertahan hingga menit akhir. namun pada satu detik terakhir terang bangsa membalikkan keadaan dengan satu poinnya yang sekaligus menutup pertandingan dengan skor 6-5. skuad sma terang bangsa (b) di ajang kali ini diawaki yonathan a l (9), yordan ezra (1), hansel r (8), dan alberto silfo (15) dipastikan melaju pada babak selanjutnya.(dan/bas)... smaga tampil perkasa 10 august 2017 tim basket cowok sman 3 semarang (smaga) akhirnya berhasil memenuhi ambisi mereka untuk melewati laga perdana honda dbl central java series north region 2017 dengan kemenangan.di laga perdana yang digelar di gor ud sumber waras (knights stadium) malam (9/8) kemarin smaga sukses menyudahi perlawanan sman 2 semarang (smanda) dengan skor yang cukup ketat 31-22.pada quarter pertama smaga mengambil inisiatif menyerang, smaga langsung memimpin dengan skor 8-0. konsistensi permainan cepat reyhan dkk membuat mereka terus memimpin hingga quarter empat.pelatih sman 3 semarang, dwi anditya mengungkapkan timnya mampu tampil maksimal meladeni smanda. smaga lebih banyak menguasai jalannya pertandingan karena kesiapan mempelajari kemampuan lawan yang lebih baik.pemain kita lebih sema ngat, menguasai jalannya pertandingan akhirnya. sebelumnya kita juga lihat video pertandingan smanda, dari situ kita belajar gaya bermainnya mereka, apa kelemahannya mereka. next saya harap sman 3 dapat melaju sampai final,bebernya.sementara kekalahan smanda diakui karena salah start. dari sisi strategi defense mereka bagus namun saat offense tidak dapat menggebrak. kita seperti telat panas. di defense kita bagus di offense kita kalah, jadi untuk kedepannya kita menguatkan keduannya, ujar pelatih smanda padang baro.sementara satu tim cowok lainnya yaitu sman 1 salatiga juga berhasil melewati laga perdana dengan kemenangan setelah mengalahkan sman 5 semarang dengan skor cukup meyakinkan yaitu 39-10.coach sman 1 salatiga rendy fernando kouwe, menerapkan permainan simple dari pertahanan terlebih dahulu. sedikit kelemahan tim yakni pada stamina, namun tim tetap bermain kompleks dengan pelan-pelan menambah poin. sejauh perjalanan tadi defense jalan baik. beberapa kali blank karena faktor stamina. next game kita persiapan fisik yang lebih baik, tandasnya.sementara coach sman 5 semarang, petrus tri f mengatakan kekalaan tim perlu dievaluasi. selanjutnya akan lebih banyak porsi latihan dengan menambah waktu. kita tahu tempo dulu dan sekarang beda, dulu pemain basket yag bagus hanya dari klub. kalau era sekarang pemain bagus dari luar klub juga bersaing. sehingga porsi latihan di sekolah itu perlu ditambah ya. kita kuatkan disitu. saya apresiasi anakanak, ujarnya. (dan/bas)... tiga tim tembus top ten 10 august 2017 tiga tim dance yaitu tim sman 1 semarang (non pendamping), sman 1 salatiga (pendamping cowok) dan sman 3 semarang (pendamping cewek) sukses mendapatkan predikat best three perform roadshow ubs gold dance competition.atas predikat tersebut ketiganya dipastikan lolos ke babak top ten ubs gold dance competition 2017 karena best three perform dalam roadshow otomatis mendapatkan tiket ke top ten. dengan begitu berarti saat ini tinggal tersisa tujuh tiket yang akan diperebutkan oleh tim dance peserta yang masih berkesempatan tampil di knights stadium.sementara tim dance pendamping basket cewek sman 1 karanganyar demak tak banyak menggunakan property yang ribet ketika perform kemarin. kostum berwarana kuning dan property caping serta selendang nyatanya membuat meraka tampil enerjik dalam ubs gold dance competition 2017 di gor sumber waras (knights stadium) kemarin.riuhan sorak-sorai ratusan penonton mengiringi penampilan mereka. aksi tim dance yang dipimpin oleh kartika tri amanda ini turut membawa tim basket mereka merebut kemenangan atas sman 4 semarang dengan skor 30-8.ajang ubs gold dance competition tahun ini jadi ajang pertamanya. tema perpaduan tradisio- nal dance dan modern dance terlihat memukau karena gerakan enerjik mereka. kita berdelapan. dan baru kali ini ikut dbl tahun kemarin belum,tapi kita semangat dukung tim basket kami, kata kartika.red blazer, tim dance pendamping tim basket cowok pun sukses tampil glamour dengan koreografi la la land yang sudah diperagakan dalam roadshow sebelumnya. dengan sorakan suporter lengkap dengan alat musik dan bendera, para dancer serasa sepesial ditengah oasis. kita sudah latihan terus, doa juga, kata kapten dance red blazer yosi setya pratini semangat.tim dance lain pun menampilkan aksi terbaiknya. apalagi bagi tim dance pendamping tim basket cowok sman 1 salatiga yang datang jauh-jauh dari salatiga. arpandu brastika dkk sukses menampilkan konsep dance dengan iringan musik timur tengah. kostum rumbairumbai aladin meneguhkan keindahan gerakan mereka yang lentur. pixel studios diseo y desarrollo web tarifas cuntanos tu proyecto tu empresa no va a funcionar con una web bonita necesitas adems que tu web est pensada para hacer su trabajo principal: vender no intentar impresionar a tus familiares y amigos, o llenar tu ego. pero s, hacemos webs preciosas que te llevarn ms y mejores clientes cada da... hay una pieza clave que nadie te dice que necesitas cuando vas a hacer una web nadie te dice que necesitas a un equipo que sepa de ventas y marketing, crees que con un diseador y un programador es suficiente por eso la mayora de webs ah fuera fracasan miserablemente. tu objetivo no debe ser un diseo espectacular, sino construir una autntica maquinaria para vender mejor, es decir, no solo vender ms, sino ahorrar tiempo en el seguimiento a tus clientes y prospectos, aportar mucho ms valor para que estn dispuestos a pagarte ms y reducir tus costes operativos. empieza a vender mejor me estis diciendo que no tendr la mejor web? en absoluto. directores de marketing o ventas, empresarios y emprendedores nos contratan para ayudarles a concebir, disear y programar todo tipo de aplicaciones o webs para vender mejor. es evidente que quieres que el diseo de tu web sea espectacular, tenga un fantstico posicionamiento en buscadores, sea fcil de usar, segura, funcione en mviles e incluya mantenimiento para mejorarla constantemente, pero esto se supone que es el mnimo aceptable que toda empresa debe ofrecerte, no? en lo que debes enfocarte es en contarnos los objetivos que deseas conseguir; ya que parte del por qu nos contratas es recomendarte la mejor y ms rpida forma de alcanzar tus objetivos. cuntanos qu quieres conseguir tarifas: "he visto empresas que hacen webs por 400" y hemos de decirte que si buscas mejor encontrars incluso gratis, pero si te ests planteando contratar a una empresa es porque necesitas algo ms que una web bonita. t decides cuanto invertir, nuestra primera tarea es proponerte el mejor proyecto posible en base a tu presupuesto. solo trabajamos con inversiones desde 2.000 a partir de ah puedes invertir lo que quieras, siempre tendremos propuestas adicionales que darte para hacer crecer an ms tu empresa. si tu proyecto requiere una inversin mayor, te lo diremos en la primera llamada. tu presupuesto es menor de 2.000? no sabes cunto invertir? quieres empezar? escrbenos... todo el mundo vende algo, pero nosotros haremos que lo vendas todo... en los ltimos 8 aos hemos creado 421 sitios webs, tiendas online, sistemas de reservas para hoteles, marketplaces, sistemas de fidelizacin para aerolneas, plataformas de juegos, aplicaciones mviles, sistemas de facturacin, redes sociales, universidades virtuales y un montn de proyectos ms en los que hemos enseado a emprendedores, empresarios y distintos equipos de trabajo a aprovechar la tecnologa para vender mejor, reducir costes operativos y tener mayor control. te enseamos cmo pero tenemos que confesarte que no trabajamos con todo el mundo... habiendo desarrollado literalmente cientos de soluciones para clientes de todo tipo y en prcticamente todas las industrias, hemos aprendido muy bien cules son los factores clave para asegurar el xito de tu proyecto... nos aseguramos de acumular desde el inicio todas las garantas posibles para lograrlo, es por esto que solo trabajaremos contigo si compartes con nosotros las siguientes condiciones: dispones de tiempo para dedicar al proyecto vamos a demandar tu completa atencin y prioridad; district. student success is the heart of our mission and we've hired the best and brightest faculty and staff to ensure that our students are well prepared when they transfer to a university, enter the workforce, or embark on a path of lifelong learning. great news! both evergreen valley college san jose city college received accreditation reaffirmation congratulations! the san jos evergreen community college district (sjeccd) learned this week that both of its colleges, evergreen valley college (evc) and san jos city college (sjcc), received reaffirmation of their accreditation status for 18 months based on a comprehensive evaluation by the accrediting commission for community and junior colleges (accjc). "reaffirmation for 18 months indicates that the commission has determined that the institution is in substantial compliance with standards," letters from accjc to the college presidents read... "the accreditation process is vital to the ongoing improvement of our colleges and we are grateful for accjc's work in ensuring that we continue to meet their high standards for institutional effectiveness," said dr. deborah budd, sjeccd chancellor. "the fact that both colleges have had their accreditation reaffirmed reflects the hard work taking place on our campuses, our commitment to continuous improvement, and the dedication of our faculty and staff to serving students." (read more...) every six years, community colleges are reviewed by the accrediting commission for community and junior colleges (commission) to ensure that all eligibility requirements, accreditation standards, and commission policies are met. evc please click the following links for the accjc's february 3, 2017 letter to evc and february 3, 2017 external evaluation team report. sjcc please click the following links for the accjc's february 3, 2017 letter to sjcc and february 3, 2017 external evaluation team report. evc names interim president a new interim president has been named for evergreen valley college (evc). keith aytch, who has served as vice president of academic affairs at evc since 2011, was appointed interim president by a unanimous vote of the san jos evergreen community college district (sjeccd) board of trustees during its july 11 meeting. "we are very fortunate to have someone of mr. aytch's caliber to serve as interim president of evc while we conduct a search for the next full-time president," said sjeccd chancellor dr. debbie budd. "evc has a strong history and a bright future and keith's qualifications, expertise, and experience will serve the college well." read more ...) san jose promise launched (san jose, calif.) yesterday, san jos evergreen community college district (sjeccd) chancellor debbie budd joined san jos mayor sam liccardo, community college presidents byron breland, henry yong, and bradley davis, and several other local elected officials and community leaders to officially launch the san jos promise, a collaborative, city-wide campaign to ensure that community college is affordable and accessible for all san jos high school students... please click here to read more event photo gallery event slideshow san jos evergreen ccd takes stand to support daca students (san jose, calif.) the san jos evergreen community college district (sjeccd) board of trustees took action during its regular meeting this week to support deferred action for childhood arrivals (daca) and other vulnerable students. a resolution passed by the board tuesday indicates that sjeccd "will assure that no confidential student records will be released without a judicial warrant, subpoena or court order" and that "all students feel welcome and safe on our campuses, regardless of immigration status." than 40 years, evergreen valley college has educated our citizenry in south san jos and milpitas. our workforce institute is a training partner with many corporations as we work to develop and maintain a vital economy in the south bay. demographic changes, economic conditions, educational reforms, and the need for preparing students for postsecondary education prompted measure g bond funded initiative to build the san jos-evergreen community college extension (formerly "joint use 21st century post-secondary education center") in milpitas. this is a joint project between sjeccd and milpitas unified school district (musd) to be completed by fall of 2016 with the following goals: 1. promote a seamless system of higher education services 2. expand access to higher education in underserved areas of the district 3. improve regional economic development opportunities by providing access to career and technical education adult education: the board of trustees and chancellor emeritus have undertaken a new strategic initiative to address the needs of adult learners by establishing a collaborative with local adult education schools and non-profit organizations. through the summer and fall of 2013, the south bay consortium for adult education (sbcae) was formed. the purpose of the consortium is to develop plans for adult education for south bay region. educating more than 20,000 students each year, our colleges are hubs of teaching, learning and innovation in one of the most exciting cities in the world. sjeccd global ends statement the san jos-evergreen community college district exists to ensure all students, especially those with educational and/or socioeconomic challenges, will have the skills and capabilities to be successful in the next stage of their life, sufficient to justify the use of available resources. please click here for ends policy dashboards sjeccd ends policies: student success the san jos-evergreen community college district will improve student success evc sjcc through enhanced educational services and programs evc sjcc wi and strengthened community engagement. included in student success: transferability (all students, especially under-prepared students, will achieve academic success sufficient to transfer evc sjcc to a four-year post-secondary institution.) college readiness students will develop the language skills to succeed in college, the ability to analyze, synthesize, and evaluate information, and will be able to effectively communicate with others and successfully work collaboratively in culturally diverse settings.) college experience (enrichment opportunities evc sjcc wi will exist to enhance the learning environment and support student success.) degree and certificate completion (students will complete degrees and certificates to enter the workforce.) sjeccd ends policies: community impact as a leader in the silicon valley, the san jos-evergreen community college district will be an acquire skills sufficient to get, keep and progress in jobs with local employers, particularly in high wage/high growth areas, for all students, especially for: under-prepared students; older guides get the latest edition: georgia in the american revolution dar publications american treasure: the enduring spirit of the dar research your family history are you just starting out on your journey to discover your family rootsor are you one document away from solving a mystery of one of your ancestors? wherever you are in your genealogical process, dar is here to help. the dar genealogical research system (grs) includes free online databases containing information on revolutionary patriot ancestors, descendants of those patriots, as well as the vast array of genealogical resources from the dar library. map your family tree find out who you're related to honor your ancestors preserve your history forever free access to our records no membership needed become a member share a bond dar members come from a variety of backgrounds and interests, but all share a common bond of having an ancestor who helped contribute to securing the independence of the united states of america. any woman 18 years or older, regardless of race, religion or ethnic background, who can prove lineal descent from a patriot of the american revolution is eligible to join. daughters are vibrant, active women who are passionate about community service, preserving history, educating children, as well as honoring and supporting those who serve our nation. learn more about the membership process fill out the membership interest form todays daughters the four founders eugenia washington mary desha ellen walworth mary s. lockwood the dar story the daughters of the american revolution is an organization with a deeply rich history while also being truly relevant in todays world. more than 930,000 women have joined the organization since it was founded close to 125 years ago. they became members to honor their heritage as well as make a difference in their communities across the country and the world. learn more about the amazing history of the dar and what members are doing today to continue that legacy. dar history work of the organization national headquarters building what's your dar story? daughters touch lives every day and make lasting impressions on their community. with 180,000 members, our stories are written on hearts globally. tell us your dar story "a dar scholarship helped me go to college." region march 24, 2017 2016 financial statements messages march 17, 2017 why i dissented neel kashkari president federal reserve bank of minneapolis the federal reserve system is the central bank of the united states. congress created the federal reserve through a law passed in 1913, charging it with a responsibility to foster a sound banking system and a healthy economy. this broad mission remains today for the federal reserve bank of minneapolis and the 11 other federal reserve banks, each serving a specific region of the country. the minneapolis fed, with one branch in helena, montana, serves the six states of the ninth federal reserve district: minnesota, montana, north and south dakota, 26 counties in northwestern wisconsin and the upper peninsula of michigan. president edita a part of everyday life about edita who we are what we do our brands our markets csr hse investor relations media advertisment photo gallery get creative recipes share your ideas careers reach us about edita who we are what we do our brands our markets csr hse investor relations media advertisment photo gallery get creative recipes share your ideas careers reach us open the menu the sweet side of life play video edita food industries a leader in the egyptian snack food market established in 1996, edita food industries is one of the leading fmcg companies in egypt and the middle east. with more than 5,680 employees and 80skus, edita holds a leading market share in each of its five segments that span the egyptian snack food market; a success driven by the companys reputation for quality and affordability. under editas production umbrella are a range of high quality products and household brand names that include, molto, todo, bake rolz, bake stix, mimix, hohos, twinkies, and tiger tail. edita also acts as the sole regional distributor of several brands of imported olive oils, and pasta. our story molto the first and generic brand name of packed croissant in egypt and neighboring countries. launched in the late 1990s, molto introduced owned a new concept of healthy yet delicious snacking to egypt. the brand is available in two croissant families (sweet savory) and pate (sweet). details todo editas newest and most premium range of cakes. with its sweet taste, variety of offering and sophisticated package, todo is positioned as the sweet experience that keeps me going. todo is a brand with 5 different families classified by color, blue for layered cake (available now in 4 variants), green for rolled cake and mini todo and,white with navy blue for todo bomb, and white with red for todo browniesand, white with light blue for todo bar which is the latest addition for todo family. details bake rolz a brand with real value offering satisfaction, wellbeing and choice to its consumers. bake rolz is baked not fried salty snack, made of 100% wheat. crunchy in every bite with a rich toasted taste. it is available in 6 flavors of the single-serve pack; salt, pizza, ketchup, chilli lemon, cheese and olives and in 3 flavors of the family-serve pack; salt, ketchup and chilli lemon. details bake stix with all the satisfaction and well-being offered by bake rolz, bake stix extends the horizon for choice as it comes in a different shape, texture and 5 unique flavors; oriental sausages, oriental spices, bbq, salt &pepper, and cheese. it is made of 100% wheat and is considered another baked not fried salty snack. details mimix mimix is editas unique range of confectionaries. available in fourfamilies, toffee, candy, jello and lollipops with its wide variety of flavors, types, shapes, colors, and unique ingredients, mimix adds a burst of craziness to everydays life. details hohos the cylindrical, frosted, cream-filled chocolate snack cakes are editas most liked snacks. they have a nice hard chocolately coating, soft and ever-so-sweet chocolate cake and all wrapped around a swirly layer of creamy filling. details twinkies twinkies are golden sponge cake with creamy filling. they give satisfaction with every bite. details tiger tail golden sponge cake with creamy filling and decorated with raspberry jelly and coconut. details freska the most premium and most indulging wafer product to ever hit the market. freska is available in 7 different types with different coatings and different fillings to match all tastes. details edita offers a wide variety of products, covering each segment of the egyptian healthy snack food market learn more find us get in touch with us through any of our corporate contacts or drop us a line if you have questions, comments or complaints. details about edita edita is a leading fmcg company in egypt the middle east. the company holds a leading market share in each of its five segments. details news and events july 16, 2017 edita food industries inaugurates e08 factory with the commissioning of its new wafer line; launches new freska offering expansion of editas production capacities and the launch of new products is part and parcel of the companys strategy to leverage innovation and r&d as it seeks to grow its market share. may 11, 2017 edita food industries reports 1q2017 earnings edita delivers solid top-line growth with revenues climbing 24.0% y-o-y in 1q2017; bottom-line likewise turns a 23.5% y-o-y growth with operating margins remaining healthy and consumers continuing to adapt to new price points. edita media gallery view our latest marketing campaigns details "edita offers a wide variety of brands, covering each segment of the egyptian healthy snack foods market" get creative view our suggestions for cool recipes to compliment your favorite edita products. whether its cakes, bakes or wafers, weve got recipes that will leave you with a scrumptious satisfaction. cool recipes view share your ideas view about edita who we are what we do our markets csr hse investor relations in the news advertisment get creative reach us careers our brands molto todo bake rolz bake stix mimix hohos twinkies tiger tail freska follow us terms conditions privacy policy edita food industries s.a.e all rights reserved.
